  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Josiah gave to the people, of the flock, lambs and kids, all for the passover offerings,.... Which be either lambs or kids of the goats, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 12:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for all that were present, to the number of 30,000; that is, 30,000 lambs or kids, which would serve 30,000 families: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and three thousand bullocks; these were for the \"chagigah\" or feast, kept on the day following the passover: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "these were of the king's substance; taken out of his flocks and herds, or bought with his money, and liberally given to the people, to such poor families as could not afford well to be at the expense of such a festival. ",
        "children": [
          {
